08:26.672 --> 08:28.173
El!

08:28.174 --> 08:30.675
Aah! Oh, oh!

08:30.676 --> 08:34.044
Oh, El. Let me
take over for a while.

08:34.046 --> 08:35.547
Oh, no, no, no, no, no.

08:35.548 --> 08:37.948
You insult my manhood.

08:37.950 --> 08:39.417
Why, El?

08:39.418 --> 08:43.388
Let a woman huff and puff
and strain her little arms,

08:43.389 --> 08:46.191
while Carlos El Puerco Valdez,
he sit around and do nothing?

08:46.192 --> 08:47.126
No, no, no.

08:47.127 --> 08:50.061
Well, at least
let me take one oar,

08:50.062 --> 08:53.565
and I'll sit beside you
for a while.

08:53.566 --> 08:56.568
Oh, that's all right.

08:56.569 --> 08:58.069
You know, I...

08:58.070 --> 09:00.572
I did miss you
while you were sleeping,

09:00.573 --> 09:02.073
my little chilly pepper.

09:02.074 --> 09:06.077
El, think we could just
dip into our food supply again?

09:06.078 --> 09:09.080
<i>Ay, querida,</i> there is only
two breath mints left.

09:09.081 --> 09:11.082
I see...

09:11.083 --> 09:13.585
Well, could we just
have a little sip of water?

09:13.586 --> 09:16.588
The canteen, she is empty.

09:16.589 --> 09:17.589
She is?
Yeah.

09:17.590 --> 09:21.593
Oh, El, why didn't
we plan this better?

09:21.594 --> 09:24.596
We should've had a big yacht
standing by, you know,

09:24.597 --> 09:26.598
just in case
the revolution failed.

09:26.599 --> 09:28.099
Oh, no, no.

09:28.100 --> 09:30.101
That would be negative thinking.

09:30.102 --> 09:31.102
Uh, true.

09:31.103 --> 09:34.105
But we would've had
food and water,

09:34.106 --> 09:36.608
and we would've had
some warm clothes.

09:36.609 --> 09:41.546
Oh, El, I am so cold.

09:41.547 --> 09:43.548
Here, hold me.

09:43.549 --> 09:46.484
Ah, no, no, no,
we can't do that.

09:46.485 --> 09:48.486
No-no-no,
we are not married.

09:48.487 --> 09:50.488
I only want to keep warm, El.

09:50.489 --> 09:55.994
Yes, but you might lead me
to the impure thoughts.

09:55.995 --> 09:57.996
Oh, no, no, no, no.

09:57.997 --> 10:00.832
How could I desecrate you,
my Madonna? No.

10:00.833 --> 10:02.835
Well, you could desecrate
me a little.

10:04.337 --> 10:06.805
No, no, no, no, no,
we cannot sin,

10:06.806 --> 10:08.306
being so close to death.

10:08.307 --> 10:10.208
Death?

10:10.209 --> 10:11.710
Well, it doesn't look good.

10:11.711 --> 10:13.712
Just think about it, you know?

10:13.713 --> 10:15.714
A few more days
in this scorching sun,

10:15.715 --> 10:17.716
and your tummy is gonna swell.

10:17.717 --> 10:19.184
Your hair will frizz up.

10:19.185 --> 10:20.685
Your eyeballs will be burned

10:20.686 --> 10:23.188
and pop out of your head.
And you'll probably die.

10:23.189 --> 10:25.691
My hair will frizz up?

10:27.660 --> 10:29.662
Well, mine does.

10:31.530 --> 10:33.898
Oh, El, look!

10:33.899 --> 10:36.334
It's the light, the dawn.

10:36.335 --> 10:41.206
Oh El, after the darkness
came the dawn.

10:41.207 --> 10:43.709
First we freeze,
and then we fry.

10:45.211 --> 10:49.214
There's got to be land
out there somewhere.

10:49.215 --> 10:50.715
There just has to be.

10:50.716 --> 10:52.550
Sure.

10:52.551 --> 10:55.553
Well... there will be.

10:55.554 --> 10:57.055
In the meantime, El,

10:57.056 --> 10:59.557
we have to keep our spirits up.

10:59.558 --> 11:01.059
Ha-ha! Yeah.

